AU  - Kanemoto, Yoshitsugu
T1  - Pricing and Investment Policies in a System of Competitive Commuter Railways
PY  - 1984
Y1  - 1984/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297785
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 51
IS  - 4
SP  - 665
EP  - 681
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper develops a simple spatial equilibrium model of a city served by competing commuter railways and analyses the effects of different transportation policies on their pricing and investment decisions. It is shown that a system of competitive railway companies does not achieve the optimal allocation. We then examine whether or not three types of government intervention, i.e. subsidies to railway companies, a rate-of-return regulation, and the ownership of residential land by railway companies, can achieve the optimal allocation.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297785
ER  - 



